articles.summary:
President Muhammadu Buhari has mourned former Chief of Naval Staff (CNS), Rear Admiral Ishaya Iko Ibrahim (retd.
), as well as a former Head of the Directorate of Military Intelligence (DMI), Brig.-Gen. Ibrahim Sabo.
The statement said: “President Buhari condoles with family of former Chief of Naval Staff, Rear Admiral Ishaya Iko Ibrahim (retd.
), who served as Flag Officer Commanding (FOC) Naval Training Command and Naval Western Command before reaching the peak of his career.
- Advertisement -“The President prays that the Almighty God will receive the souls of the departed former military officers, and comfort their families,” the statement said.
